modules.description: This module supports 32-bit arithmetic and bitwise operations, including addition, multiplication, shifts, and logical operations, using register-register or register-immediate operands. It operates on 32-bit registers (`EBPF.reg`) within eBPF instructions (`EBPF.insn`), providing foundational capabilities for low-level program logic. These operations are essential for implementing network packet filtering, system monitoring, or custom kernel-space computations in eBPF programs.

This module provides low-level operations for constructing eBPF programs, including memory access, control flow, and arithmetic/bitwise manipulations. It operates on eBPF registers and immediate integer values, supporting 32-bit and 64-bit operations alongside byte-order conversions for kernel-level networking or tracing applications. Specific use cases include implementing packet filters, system call tracing, and performance monitoring tools requiring precise register-level control.
